_Pa’al_ Future Tense for regular shorushim:
The [[_pa’al_ future tense]] follows these conjugations for [[regular shorushim]]:
|| *Singular* |\<| *Plural* |\< |
| *First-Person* | אֶכְתֹּב<br>_echtoiv_<br>I will write | \< | נִכְתֹּב<br>_nichtoiv_<br>We will write | \< |
| *Second-Person* | תִּכְתֹּב <br>_tichtov_<br> You [male] will write | תִּכְתְּבִי <br>_tichtevi_<br> You [female] will write  | תִּכְתְּבוּ <br>_tichtevu_<br> You [males] will write  | תִּכְתֹּבְנָה <br>_tichtoivnau_<br> You [females] will write  |
| *Third-Person* | יִכְתֹּב <br>_yichtoiv_<br> He will write | תִּכְתֹּב <br>_tichtov_<br> She will write  | יִכְתְּבוּ <br>_yichtevu_<br> [Those males] will write  | תִּכְתֹּבְנָה <br>_tichtoivnau_<br> [Those females] will write  |
For any regular shoresh, you can replace the letters ‎כ, ‎ת, and ב above with the letters of your shoresh to produce the proper conjugations.
